# Cursor Rules for Text-to-Video Project

## Container Registry Preferences
- Use GitHub Container Registry (ghcr.io) when possible for storing and deploying container images
- Prefer GitHub Container Registry over other registries like Docker Hub, AWS ECR, or Google Artifact Registry when feasible

## AI Model Hub Preferences
- Use Hugging Face Hub when possible for accessing pre-trained models, datasets, and AI components
- Prefer Hugging Face transformers and diffusers libraries for AI model implementations

## Technology Stack Requirements
- Always use CUDA 12.8 for GPU acceleration through system packages and PyTorch cu128 wheels
- Always use Python 3.12 as the standard Python version across all services
- Install PyTorch with CUDA 12.8 support using: pip install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128
- Prefer BentoML's default base images with CUDA and Python installed as system packages for better compatibility
- Ensure all Docker images, virtual environments, and dependencies are compatible with these versions

## Project Configuration Standards
- Always use email: the.dsvolk@icloud.com for author information in project files
